race.comment: With SKETCH running and winning yesterday, HOT BLUE (7) has a royal chance to win on debut. The Hayes-trained colt has three jumpouts under the saddle, and one of Australia's best jockeys is engaged. That's a decent push for his chances. WETLAND (12) settled well back at Ballarat on debut and impressed with her finishing effort over 1200m. She's sure to appreciate the longer sprint and maps better today. A live chance. OCTOBER MANIFESTO (8) has his third race start and will appreciate the longer sprint. He's in good hands and a senior jockey is aboard today. HARRY DEVIL (3) peaks and likely has excuses at Echuca. Has the blinkers on for the first time, and they may spark some of the extra required.
